channel.title: Does this help at all for the new RS Client?
channel.description:
Knowing the members here, you guys must already have this information since it was pretty simple to obtain, but if you never thought of it. Here it is. :)
I looked through the source code and found several downloadable files. After downloading, and decompiling, you can see the source code.
[url=http://se2.runescape.com/lang/en/aff/runescape/loader-780769402.jar]loader-780769402.jar[/url] - Downloadable [url=http://se2.runescape.com/lang/en/aff/runescape/loader-223975276.cab]loader-223975276.cab[/url] - Downloadable and unzip with WinRar [url=http://se2.runescape.com/lang/en/aff/runescape/plugin.js?lowmem=1=0]plugin.js?lowmem=1=0[/url] - All you see on this one are several document.write(''); but if you look through the source code, you get the param information. [url=http://se2.runescape.com/lang/en/aff/runescape/loader.class]loader.class[/url] - This one is interesting and it's in the code, but I get a 404 when I access it.
Freeware decompilers can be found here. I think they are all trials though. Sorry, couldn't find any torrents. [url=http://members.fortunecity.com/neshkov/dj.html]DJ Java Decompiler[/url] [url=http://www.brouhaha.com/~eric/software/mocha/]Mocha Decompiler[/url] [url=http://www.bysoft.se/sureshot/cavaj/]Cavaj Decompiler[/url]
[url=http://validator.w3.org/check?uri=http%3A%2F%2Fse2.runescape.com%2Flang%2Fen%2Faff%2Frunescape%2Fgame.ws%3Flowmem%3D1%26plugin%3D0&charset=%28detect+automatically%29&doctype=Inline&sp=1]And here is a source code for the random world I chose.[/url] - Just scroll down passed the errors and onto the parsed code tree.
I hope I helped.
~Ron
